Hi @don750421!

With that code, if ajax is used more than once, tablesorter won't reinitialize correctly. The contents of the table are being cleared, but not the parameters saved to the `table`  element. Try moving the `id="info" to the wrapper div, then append the response with a table wrap:

```html
<div id="info" style="overflow:auto; width:500px; height:150px"></div> 
```

```js
success: function( response ) {
    $('#info').html( '<table>' + response + '</table>' );

    $('#info table').tablesorter({
        ...
    })
    .tablesorterPager({
        ...
    });
}
```

If you don't want to use the `auto` feature, you can set the [`columnSelector_mediaquery` option](http://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/example-widget-column-selector.html#column-selector-mediaquery) to `false`.

If you want the column selector to start out with the `auto` feature unchecked, then set the [`columnSelector_mediaqueryState` option](http://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/example-widget-column-selector.html#column-selector-mediaquery-state) to `false`.

